sql:
SELECT COUNT(config_id) AS config_count
FROM simulation_configs
WHERE user_id = 123;

SELECT config_name, created_date
FROM simulation_configs
ORDER BY created_date DESC;

SELECT config_name
FROM simulation_configs
WHERE user_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- Completed simulation runs refer to runs with a status of 'completed';
- The "latest" simulation run is determined by the most recent end time for each configuration;
- The convergence status indicates whether the measure converged during the simulation run.

sql:
SELECT param_name, description
FROM simulation_params
WHERE default_value IS NOT NULL;
